ablished in 1796]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1929]]\n[[Category:1708 establishments in Russia]]\n[[Category:1726 establishments in the Russian Empire]]\n[[Category:Governorates of the Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]\n", "name_user": "Alphathon", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smolensk_Governorate"}
{"title_page": "Outline of Romania", "text_new": "{{Short description|1=Overview of and topical guide to Romania}}\n{{See also|Index of Romania-related articles}}\n<!--... Attention:  THIS IS AN OUTLINE\n\n        part of the set of 740+ outlines listed at\n             [[Portal:Contents/Outlines]].\n\n                 Wikipedia outlines are\n              a special type of list article.\n              They make up one of Wikipedia's\n                content navigation systems\n\n                See [[Wikipedia:Outlines]]\n                      for more details.\n                   Further improvements\n              to this outline are on the way\n...-->\n{{multiple image\n| align = right\n| image1 = Flag of Romania.svg\n| width1 = 192\n| alt1 = \n| caption1 = The [[Flag of Romania]]\n| image2 = Coat of arms of Romania.svg\n| width2 = 93\n| alt2 = \n| caption2 = The [[Coat of arms of Romania]]\n| footer = \n}}\n[[File:LocationRomania - Cold War.png|thumb|The location of [[Romania]]]]\n[[File:Un-romania.png|thumb|An enlargeable map of [[Romania]]]]\n\nThe following [[Outline (list)|outline]] is provided as an overview of and topical guide to Romania:\n\n'''[[Romania]]''' &ndash; unitary semi-presidential republic located in [[Central Europe|Central]]-[[Southeast Europe|Southeastern Europe]], bordering the Black Sea, between Bulgaria and Ukraine. It also borders Hungary, Serbia, and Moldova. It covers 238,391 square kilometres (92,043 sq mi) and has a temperate-continental climate. With 19.9 million inhabitants, it is the seventh most populous member of the European Union. Its capital and largest city, Bucharest, is the sixth largest city in the EU. It encompasses the historical regions of [[Wallachia]] (including [[Dobruja]]), [[Moldavia]] (including [[Bukovina]]), [[Transylvania]] (including [[Banat]], [[Maramure\u0219]], and [[Cri\u0219ana]]). ''Romania''  derives from the Latin ''romanus'', meaning [[Ancient Rome|\"citizen of Rome\"]].\n\n{{TOC limit|limit=2}}\n\n==General reference==\n[[File:Romania 1994 CIA map 1.png|thumb|An enlargeable relief map of [[Romania]]]]\n* [[International Phonetic Alphabet|Pronunciation]]:\n* Common English country name:  [[Romania]]\n* Official English country name:  [[Romania]]\n* Common [[endonym]](s): [[List of countries and capitals in native languages|Rom\u00e2nia]]\n* Official endonym(s): [[List of official endonyms of present-day nations and states|Rom\u00e2n]]\n* [[List of adjectival and demonymic forms of place names#Countries and nations|Adjectival]](s): [[Romanian (disambiguation)|Romanian]] <!-- This disambiguation page is the only page on Wikipedia that specifically explains this term and its country adjectival contexts, and it does so excellently.  Please leave this link in place. -->\n* [[List of adjectival and demonymic forms of place names#Countries and nations|Demonym]](s): Romanian\n* [[Etymology]]: [[Name of Romania]]\n* [[ISO country codes]]:  RO, ROU, 642\n* [[ISO region codes]]:  See [[ISO 3166-2:RO]]\n* [[Internet]] [[country code top-level domain]]:  [[.ro]]\n\n==Geography of Romania==\n[[File:Romania general map.png|thumb|An enlargeable general map of [[Romania]]]]\n\n[[Geography of Romania]]\n* Romania is: a [[country]]\n* Location:\n** [[Northern Hemisphere]] and [[Eastern Hemisphere]]\n** [[Eurasia]]\n*** Europe\n**** [[Central Europe]]\n**** [[Eastern Europe]]\n** [[Time zone]]:  [[Eastern European Time]] ([[UTC+02]]), [[Eastern European Summer Time]] ([[UTC+03]])\n** [[Extreme points of Romania]]\n*** High:  [[Moldoveanu Peak|Moldoveanu]] {{convert|2544|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}\n*** Low:  [[Black Sea]] 0 m\n** Land boundaries:  2,508&nbsp;km\n::{{Flag|Bulgaria}} 608 km\n::{{Flag|Ukraine}} 531 km\n::{{Flag|Serbia}} 476 km\n::{{Flag|Moldova}} 450 km\n::{{Flag|Hungary}} 443 km\n:* Coastline:  [[Black Sea]] 225 km\n* [[Population of Romania]]: 19,638,000 (2017) - [[List of countries by population|58st most populous country]]\n* [[Area of Romania]]: 238,391&nbsp;km<sup>2</su