mperate-continental climate. With 19.9 million inhabitants, it is the seventh most populous member of the European Union. Its capital and largest city, Bucharest, is the sixth largest city in the EU. It encompasses the historical regions of [[Wallachia]] (including [[Dobruja]]), [[Moldavia]] (including [[Bukovina]]), [[Transylvania]] (including [[Banat]], [[Maramure\u0219]], and [[Cri\u0219ana]]). ''Romania''  derives from the Latin ''romanus'', meaning [[Ancient Rome|\"citizen of Rome\"]].\n\n{{TOC limit|limit=2}}\n\n==General reference==\n[[File:Romania 1994 CIA map 1.png|thumb|An enlargeable relief map of [[Romania]]]]\n* [[International Phonetic Alphabet|Pronunciation]]:\n* Common English country name:  [[Romania]]\n* Official English country name:  [[Romania]]\n* Common [[endonym]](s): [[List of countries and capitals in native languages|Rom\u00e2nia]]\n* Official endonym(s): [[List of official endonyms of present-day nations and states|Rom\u00e2n]]\n* [[List of adjectival and demonymic forms of place names#Countries and nations|Adjectival]](s): [[Romanian (disambiguation)|Romanian]] <!-- This disambiguation page is the only page on Wikipedia that specifically explains this term and its country adjectival contexts, and it does so excellently.  Please leave this link in place. -->\n* [[List of adjectival and demonymic forms of place names#Countries and nations|Demonym]](s): Romanian\n* [[Etymology]]: [[Name of Romania]]\n* [[ISO country codes]]:  RO, ROU, 642\n* [[ISO region codes]]:  See [[ISO 3166-2:RO]]\n* [[Internet]] [[country code top-level domain]]:  [[.ro]]\n\n==Geography of Romania==\n[[File:Romania general map.png|thumb|An enlargeable general map of [[Romania]]]]\n\n[[Geography of Romania]]\n* Romania is: a [[country]]\n* Location:\n** [[Northern Hemisphere]] and [[Eastern Hemisphere]]\n** [[Eurasia]]\n*** Europe\n**** [[Central Europe]]\n**** [[Eastern Europe]]\n** [[Time zone]]:  [[Eastern European Time]] ([[UTC+02]]), [[Eastern European Summer Time]] ([[UTC+03]])\n** [[Extreme points of Romania]]\n*** High:  [[Moldoveanu Peak|Moldoveanu]] {{convert|2544|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}\n*** Low:  [[Black Sea]] 0 m\n** Land boundaries:  2,508&nbsp;km\n::{{Flag|Bulgaria}} 608 km\n::{{Flag|Ukraine}} 531 km\n::{{Flag|Serbia}} 476 km\n::{{Flag|Moldova}} 450 km\n::{{Flag|Hungary}} 443 km\n:* Coastline:  [[Black Sea]] 225 km\n* [[Population of Romania]]: 19,638,000 (2017) - [[List of countries by population|58st most populous country]]\n* [[Area of Romania]]: 238,391&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>\n* [[:commons:Atlas of Romania|Atlas of Romania]]\n\n===Environment of Romania===\n[[File:Satellite image of Romania.jpg|thumb|An enlargeable satellite image of [[Romania]]]]\n\n* [[Climate of Romania]]\n* [[Environmental issues in Romania]]\n* [[Renewable energy in Romania]]\n* [[Geology of Romania]]\n* [[Protected areas of Romania]]\n* [[Wildlife of Romania]]\n** [[Flora of Romania]]\n** [[Fauna of Romania]]\n*** [[List of birds of Romania|Birds of Romania]]\n*** [[List of mammals of Romania|Mammals of Romania]]\n\n====Geographic features of Romania====\n{{Main|List of landforms of Romania|l1=Landforms of Romania}}\n\n* [[Glaciers of Romania]]\n* [[List of islands of Romania|Islands of Romania]]\n* [[List of lakes in Romania|Lakes of Romania]]\n* [[List of mountains in Romania|Mountains of Romania]]\n* [[List of rivers of Romania|Rivers of Romania]]\n* [[List of World Heritage Sites in Europe#Romania|World Heritage Sites in Romania]]\n\n===Regions of Romania===\n{{main|Regions of Romania (disambiguation){{!}}Regions of Romania}}\n\n====Administrative divisions of Romania====\n[[Administrative divisions of Romania]]\n* [[Regions of Romania (disambiguation)|Regions of Romania]]\n** [[Counties of Romania]]\n*** [[Municipalities of Romania]]\n\n=====Regions of Romania=====\n[[File:Regiuni de dezvoltare.svg|thumb|300px|Map of the development regions]]\n\n[[Development regions of Romania]]\nThese are the 8 development regions in Romania, which (with the 